fe", "comment": "Fix typo, hyphenate compound adjective", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Balut_(food)"}
{"title_page": "Tropic Skincare", "text_new": "{{short description|British skincare company}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2017}}\n{{COI|date=November 2017}}\n{{Infobox company\n| name                = Tropic Skincare\n| logo                = Tropic-Logo-Grey-Primary.png\n| type                = [[Limited company]]\n| founded             = 2011 in [[London, England|London]], England\n| founder             = [[Susie Ma]]\n| hq_location         = [[Croydon]]\n| hq_location_city    = \n| hq_location_country = England\n| area_served         = United Kingdom\n| key_people          = [[Susie Ma]] (Founder, Managing Director)\n[[Alan Sugar]]<br>(Co-Director)\n| products            = [[Skin care]], cosmetics, makeup\n| num_employees       = 160 (2019) <ref>https://www.fasttrack.co.uk/company_profile/tropic-skincare-4/</ref>\n| brands              = \n| services            = \n| owner               = <!-- or: | owners = -->\n| ratio               = <!-- for BANKS ONLY -->\n| rating              = <!-- for BANKS ONLY -->\n| net_income          = \u00a334.9 million (2019)<ref>https://www.fasttrack.co.uk/company_profile/tropic-skincare-4/</ref>\n| website             = {{URL|tropicskincare.com/}}\n}}\n\n'''Tropic Skincare''', often just referred to as Tropic, is a British [[direct selling]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cosmeticsbusiness.com/news/article_page/Tropic_Skincare_opens_first_charity-funded_school_in_Cambodia/163854|title=Tropic Skincare opens first charity-funded school in Cambodia|website=www.cosmeticsbusiness.com|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref> company which sells skincare and cosmetic products. The company does research at its London headquarters, where it designs, manufactures, markets, and distributes its products.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nme.com/news/tv/lord-sugar-invests-in-former-apprentice-candidate-872578|title=Lord Sugar invests in former 'Apprentice' candidate Susan Ma - NME|date=2012-03-19|work=NME|access-date=2017-11-23|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nTropic was informally established in 2004, when founder [[Susan Ma]] aged 15, sold a single body care product in Greenwich market, inspired by her upbringing of Tropical North Queensland.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.ok.co.uk/awards/beauty-awards/1191054/five-bath-and-shower-favourites|title=Five bath oils and shower favourites that will completely change your bathroom experien|last=Asprou|first=Helena|date=2017-10-03|work=OK! Magazine|access-date=2017-11-23}}</ref> The company officially became incorporated in 2011.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://beta.companieshouse.gov.uk/company/07840950/filing-history|title=TROPIC SKIN CARE LIMITED - Filing history (free information from Companies House)|website=beta.companieshouse.gov.uk|language=en|access-date=2017-11-23}}</ref> After Susan Ma took part in the seventh series of [[The Apprentice (UK TV series)|The Apprentice]], [[Alan Sugar]] invested to become a 50/50 partner in Tropic. In 2013, Tropic launched its Social Selling Business Platform with 400 founding sales people.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://startups.co.uk/startups-awards/product-business-of-the-year-2015/|title=Product Business of the Year 2015 - Startups Awards by Startups.co.uk: Start up a successful business|date=2015-11-27|work=Startups Awards by Startups.co.uk: Start up a successful business|access-date=2017-11-23|language=en-US}}</ref> Since then, Tropic has increased its product range to include skincare, body care, hair care, sun care, tanning serums and products designed for men,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://issuu.com/tropicskincare/docs/2018_issue12-onlinecatalogue|title=Tropic Skincare Spring 2018 Catalogue|work=Issuu|access-date=2018-05-08|language=en}}</ref> by introducing new ranges on a bi-annual basis.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://startups.co.uk/startups-awards/startups-hall-of-fame-susan-ma-tropic-skincare/|title=Startups Awards Hall of Fame: Susan Ma, Tropic Skin Care - Startups Awards by Startups.co.uk: Start up a successful business|date=2016-09-14|work=Startups Awards by Startups.co.uk: Start up a successful business|access-date=2017-11-28|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n==Business structure==\nTropic uses a [[direct sales]] and network marketing business model, in which sales people host [[party plan]] events where customers can try the products before purchasing. Sales people also can attend commercial events and have personal web-shops, where products are sold online.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://startups.co.uk/product-idea-tropic-skincare/|title=Product idea #16: Tropic Skincare {{!}} Startups.co.uk|date=2017-08-03|work=Startups.co.uk: Starting a business advice and business ideas|access-date=2017-11-23|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n\n==Ingredients==\nTropic's products are composed of naturally derived ingredients. Tropic's products do not contain [[parabens]], [[ethanol|alcohol]], [[gluten]], synthetic [[preservatives]], or [[sodium lauryl sulfate]]. All products are [[vegan]] ,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tropicskincare.com/beliefs-and-values |title=Beliefs and Values |publisher=Tropicskincare.com |accessdate=2016-09-25}}</ref> and many contain [[essential oil]]s such as [[bergamot oil]], rosehip oil, in conjunction with [[aloe vera]] juice and [[shea butter]] which are also prevalent throughout the range.\n\n== Ethics ==\nTropic is certified by the [[The Vegan Society|Vegan Society]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.vegansociety.com/search/products?search_api_views_fulltext=&search_api_views_fulltext_1=Tropic%20skincare&created=&include_brand_company=TRUE|title=Search|work=The Vegan Society|access-date=2017-11-28|language=en}}</ref> [[PETA]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.peta.org/living/beauty/search-cruelty-free-companies-products/|title=Search for Cruelty-Free Companies, Products, and More|date=2010-06-09|website=PETA|access-date=2017-11-28}}</ref> and [[Cruelty Free International]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.crueltyfreeinternational.org/cruelty-free-company/tropic-skin-care|title=Tropic Skin Care {{!}} Cruelty Free International|website=www.crueltyfreeinternational.org|access-date=2017-11-28}}</ref> and is a CarbonNeutral and Ethically accredited company <ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Z4nAqQJARhw</ref>  In 2020, Tropic opened its first charity-funded school in Cambodia.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cosmeticsbusiness.com/news/article_page/Tropic_Skincare_opens_first_charity-funded_school_in_Cambodia/163854|title=Tropic Skincare opens first charity-funded school in Cambodia|website=www.cosmeticsbusiness.com|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n\n==Awards==\n\nTropic has received the Best Business Award 2016,<ref>http://www.bestbusinessawards.co.uk/feedback.asp</ref> the 2017 Sunday Times Virgin Fast Track 100 Best Emerging Brand,<ref>{{Citation|last=Track|first=Fast|title=2017 Sunday Times Virgin Fast Track 100 conference &amp; awards dinner|date=2017-05-29|url=https://vimeo.com/219346573|accessdate=2017-07-03}}</ref> the Beauty Shortlist Award,<ref>http://www.thebeautyshortlist.com/2017-beauty-shortlist-awards-2nd-march-the-complete-winners-list/</ref> and 8 Stevie Awards including Fastest Growing Company of the Year.<ref>http://stevieawards.com/women/2016-stevie-award-winners</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://stevieawards.com/women/2017-stevie-award-winners|title=2017 Stevie Award Winners {{!}} Stevie Awards|website=stevieawards.com|language=en|access-date=2018-02-19}}</ref> In January 2018 Founder and CEO Susie Ma secured a spot on 2018 Forbes 30 Under 30 list.<ref>{{Citation|last=McGregor|first=Kirsten Taggart,Jay|title=Susan Ma: How Homemade Skincare Became A Major Beauty Business|url=https://www.forbes.com/video/5715762961001/|language=en|accessdate=2018-02-19}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Manufacturing companies based in London]]\n[[Category:Companies established in 2007]]\n[[Category:British brands]]\n[[Category:Cosmetics brands]]\n[[Category:Cosmetics companies of the United Kingdom]]\n", "text_old": "{{short descr